            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText"></span>After my time in Seattle, I lived with my parents again, which was very special. My dad had remodeled the bedroom area of the house and added a room for me and included the first bathroom upstairs and remodeled one of those two bedrooms in the front of the house into a kitchen upstairs for mother. The stairs going down to the old basement area were taken out and this made the living room about three feet wider…and my, but that living room seemed big! My dad always did his own carpentry and the old house on 16th Street shows evidence of his handwork. I also had several pieces of simple furniture that my dad made for me: a bookshelf and a small stool, both of which I still have after all these years.<br />
            </span>

            <!--div id="ChapterPictureGallery" class="clearfix">
