            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText"></span>After Ken and I met, we began to date in the spring of 1948. Ken was a farmer and had been born and raised on a farm in the farming community of Milo which is east of Idaho Falls, off the Ririe highway. He courted me in a green pickup which was not “cool” at that time. I was a bit embarrassed to be seen in the “green monster” as I called it but it was all that was available for our use and it was his totally and not his Dad's so there was some advantage to having it. 
