            <span id="ChapterParagraphTwo">
                We went to the tri-stake dances which were a main source of entertainment those days. We were involved in church activities, went to movies and lots of picnics together. Ken was quite a dancer and due to his ability to move his feet so fast while dancing the jitterbug and such that he was known as Tanglefoot at the dances and did attract a bit of attention. The foxtrot and waltz were the dances popular those days and we loved to dance. 


